Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Dip chicken pieces into 1/4 cup melted butter and place in a 9x13 inch baking dish. Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for 30 minutes. In a medium bowl combine remaining 1/4 cup melted butter with paprika, salt, mustard, chili powder, cayenne pepper water; mix together and pour mixture over chicken. Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for another 30 minutes.